The paper discusses the generalization properties of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in various fields of computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also establishes a theoretical framework for analyzing the generalization properties of these networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
